Preheat your oven to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with 0.5 tsp of @salt{0.5%tsp}. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks. Pop the @broccoli florets{200} on a #baking tray{} (chop any larger florets in half) drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Pop the potatoes on a large baking tray in a single layer. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking. Add the @penne pasta{200} to the boiling water and simmer until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan and drizzle with @olive oil{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{120} and stir fry until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from your pan to a large #bowl{} with a #slotted spoon{} (leave the oil behind in the pan). Pop your pan back on medium high heat and add the @diced chicken thigh{390}. Season with @black pepper{} and fry until the chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Add to the bowl with the bacon.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once you've turned the potatoes, roast the broccoli on the middle shelf of your oven until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Then remove and pop the @cavolo nero{100}(chopped) on top. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Pop back on the middle shelf of your oven to roast until the cavolo nero is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Meanwhile, add the @green pesto{1} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40} to the pasta. Add 2 portions of chicken and bacon and stir together (this is for your lunch).

Put the @wholegrain mustard{1} and @honey{15} into a bowl with the @olive oil{1} (see ingredients for amount). Mix together. Once cooked, add the potatoes to the large bowl with the remaining chicken and bacon. Add in all but a small handful of the greens. Pour in the dressing and gently toss to coat. Serve the chicken, bacon and potato toss in bowl, top with a spoonful of @soured cream{150} and the remaining cheese. Sprinkle over the @walnuts{20} and enjoy!

Add the remaining veg to the pan with the pasta and gently stir together. Add salt and pepper to taste. Divide between containers, cover and pop in your fridge for your lunch the next day - once ready to eat, reheat until piping hot in the microwave or enjoy cold.